{
  "stem": "10587.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Our-- our place of worship, this is-- you know, the main-- the main synagogue of town, which has been-- I don't know exactly how old it was.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it was a nice and beautiful synagogue.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was-- a-- there were other synagogues-- there were other [INAUDIBLE], what they called, and also house of prayers, mainly [INAUDIBLE], where more Hasidic than ultra Orthodox people would-- would go.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Synagogue was already more sort of, I would, say reform.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it was maybe a little bit more modern because it was a beautiful structure.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It had [INAUDIBLE] and [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "A [INAUDIBLE] usually had benches and tables and maybe a little credenza to hold the Sefer Torah.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But-- or some kind of a arc, but the synagogue had to be beautiful [INAUDIBLE] with the arc with the-- in the Sefer Torah.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So-- the--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I felt like-- like-- like the-- this is a place where I was going to pray, where I was going to school and learn about the [INAUDIBLE], Russia and-- and about the five books of Moses, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that this-- what am I going to do now?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Where-- where-- where do I go from here?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I felt like I was-- there was a terrible violation to-- to my education.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I was going to public school, too.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I was going to elementary school, which was total opposite direction from the-- from the synagogue, but since we were so centrally located, so for me it was maybe a little bit further to the public school, but we-- then-- then went to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Synagogue was very close.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, the schools-- no, you were not allowed to go to school.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't even think that the schools were open.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And after the Germans occupied our town, I don't think so.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
